        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "json"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Common field patterns\n\n// 1. Check a tag exists and has a specific value\n{\n  \"field\": \"tags['Environment']\",\n  \"in\": [\"prod\", \"production\"]\n}\n\n// 2. Case-insensitive string match using 'like'\n{\n  \"field\": \"Microsoft.Compute/virtualMachines/storageProfile.imageReference.offer\",\n  \"like\": \"Windows*\"\n}\n\n// 3. Check that a tag does NOT exist (negated existence check)\n{\n  \"not\": {\n    \"field\": \"tags['Owner']\",\n    \"exists\": \"true\"\n  }\n}\n\n// 4. Match by SKU tier across multiple allowed values\n{\n  \"field\": \"Microsoft.Storage/storageAccounts/sku.name\",\n  \"notIn\": [\"Standard_LRS\", \"Premium_LRS\"]\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Count Expressions for Array Properties"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Many Azure resource properties are arrays \u2014 NSG security rules, disk configurations, subnet associations. A field condition cannot test individual array elements; for that, the count expression iterates the array and applies a nested where condition to each element. The result of a count expression is an integer that you then compare using a numeric operator."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "json"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Deny NSGs that have ANY inbound rule allowing port 22 from the internet\n{\n  \"if\": {\n    \"allOf\": [\n      {\n        \"field\": \"type\",\n        \"equals\": \"Microsoft.Network/networkSecurityGroups\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"count\": {\n          \"field\": \"Microsoft.Network/networkSecurityGroups/securityRules[*]\",\n          \"where\": {\n            \"allOf\": [\n              {\n                \"field\": \"Microsoft.Network/networkSecurityGroups/securityRules[*].direction\",\n                \"equals\": \"Inbound\"\n              },\n              {\n                \"field\": \"Microsoft.Network/networkSecurityGroups/securityRules[*].access\",\n                \"equals\": \"Allow\"\n              },\n              {\n                \"field\": \"Microsoft.Network/networkSecurityGroups/securityRules[*].destinationPortRange\",\n                \"equals\": \"22\"\n              },\n              {\n                \"field\": \"Microsoft.Network/networkSecurityGroups/securityRules[*].sourceAddressPrefix\",\n                \"in\": [\"*\", \"Internet\", \"0.0.0.0/0\"]\n              }\n            ]\n          }\n        },\n        \"greater\": 0\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"then\": { \"effect\": \"deny\" }\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The then Block and Effect Details"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The then block contains a single effect key (a string or parameter reference) and an optional details key used by AuditIfNotExists and DeployIfNotExists. The effect determines what the policy engine does when the if condition is true. Effects that operate at ARM request time (Deny, Append, Modify) are synchronous. Effects that check or deploy companion resources (AuditIfNotExists, DeployIfNotExists) are asynchronous \u2014 they run during background compliance evaluation, not at request time."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "json"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// AINE: check that a diagnostic setting exists on Key Vault\n{\n  \"if\": {\n    \"field\": \"type\",\n    \"equals\": \"Microsoft.KeyVault/vaults\"\n  },\n  \"then\": {\n    \"effect\": \"AuditIfNotExists\",\n    \"details\": {\n      \"type\": \"Microsoft.Insights/diagnosticSettings\",\n      \"existenceCondition\": {\n        \"allOf\": [\n          {\n            \"count\": {\n              \"field\": \"Microsoft.Insights/diagnosticSettings/logs[*]\",\n              \"where\": {\n                \"field\": \"Microsoft.Insights/diagnosticSettings/logs[*].enabled\",\n                \"equals\": \"true\"\n              }\n            },\n            \"greater\": 0\n          },\n          {\n            \"field\": \"Microsoft.Insights/diagnosticSettings/workspaceId\",\n            \"equals\": \"[parameters('logAnalyticsWorkspaceId')]\"\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n// DINE: deploy a Log Analytics agent extension\n{\n  \"then\": {\n    \"effect\": \"DeployIfNotExists\",\n    \"details\": {\n      \"type\": \"Microsoft.Compute/virtualMachines/extensions\",\n      \"roleDefinitionIds\": [\n        \"/providers/Microsoft.Authorization/roleDefinitions/b24988ac-6180-42a0-ab88-20f7382dd24c\"\n      ],\n      \"existenceCondition\": {\n        \"allOf\": [\n          { \"field\": \"Microsoft.Compute/virtualMachines/extensions/publisher\", \"equals\": \"Microsoft.Azure.Monitor\" },\n          { \"field\": \"Microsoft.Compute/virtualMachines/extensions/type\", \"equals\": \"AzureMonitorWindowsAgent\" },\n          { \"field\": \"Microsoft.Compute/virtualMachines/extensions/provisioningState\", \"in\": [\"Succeeded\", \"Provisioning succeeded\"] }\n        ]\n      },\n      \"deployment\": {\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"mode\": \"incremental\",\n          \"template\": { \"/* ARM template to deploy the extension */\": \"\" }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Parameters in Policy Rules"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Parameters are declared in the parameters section of the policy definition (outside policyRule) and injected into policyRule using the [parameters('name')] ARM function syntax. Parameters can have types: String, Array, Boolean, Integer, Object, or Float. Providing allowedValues restricts what can be passed at assignment time, which is the primary mechanism for making policies configurable without modifying the rule itself."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "json"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\n  \"parameters\": {\n    \"effect\": {\n      \"type\": \"String\",\n      \"defaultValue\": \"Audit\",\n      \"allowedValues\": [\"Audit\", \"Deny\", \"Disabled\"],\n      \"metadata\": { \"displayName\": \"Effect\", \"description\": \"Audit, Deny, or Disabled\" }\n    },\n    \"allowedLocations\": {\n      \"type\": \"Array\",\n      \"defaultValue\": [\"eastus\", \"eastus2\", \"westus2\"],\n      \"metadata\": {\n        \"displayName\": \"Allowed locations\",\n        \"strongType\": \"location\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"logAnalyticsWorkspaceId\": {\n      \"type\": \"String\",\n      \"metadata\": {\n        \"displayName\": \"Log Analytics workspace resource ID\",\n        \"strongType\": \"omsWorkspace\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"tagName\": {\n      \"type\": \"String\",\n      \"metadata\": { \"displayName\": \"Tag name to require\" }\n    }\n  },\n  \"policyRule\": {\n    \"if\": {\n      \"allOf\": [\n        { \"field\": \"type\", \"in\": [\"[parameters('resourceTypes')]\"] },\n        { \"field\": \"location\", \"notIn\": \"[parameters('allowedLocations')]\" }\n      ]\n    },\n    \"then\": {\n      \"effect\": \"[parameters('effect')]\"\n    }\n  }\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Policy Aliases: Mapping to Resource Properties"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An alias is the string path used in the field key to reference a specific resource property. Azure Policy maintains an alias catalog that maps human-readable paths to the underlying ARM REST API property paths. Finding the correct alias is often the hardest part of writing a custom policy \u2014 guessing the path rarely works because the alias namespace follows the ARM resource provider hierarchy, not the portal UI."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# List ALL aliases for a specific resource type\naz policy alias list \\\n  --namespace Microsoft.Compute \\\n  --resource-type virtualMachines \\\n  --query '[].name' -o tsv | sort | head -40\n\n# Find aliases matching a keyword (e.g., find all aliases with 'sku' in the path)\naz policy alias list \\\n  --namespace Microsoft.Storage \\\n  --resource-type storageAccounts \\\n  --query \"[?contains(name, 'sku')].name\" -o tsv\n\n# Check if an alias is modifiable (required for Modify and Append effects)\naz policy alias list \\\n  --namespace Microsoft.Compute \\\n  --resource-type virtualMachines \\\n  --query \"[?name=='Microsoft.Compute/virtualMachines/networkProfile.networkInterfaces[*].id'].{Alias:name,Modifiable:defaultMetadata.attributes}\" \\\n  -o table\n\n# View alias with API version context (important for array aliases)\naz policy alias list \\\n  --namespace Microsoft.Network \\\n  --resource-type networkSecurityGroups \\\n  --query \"[?contains(name,'securityRules')].{Alias:name,APIVersions:pathMetadata[].apiVersions[0]}\" \\\n  -o table\n\n# Commonly used aliases for reference:\n# type                                          -> resource type\n# name                                          -> resource name\n# location                                      -> resource region\n# tags['tagName']                               -> specific tag value\n# Microsoft.Compute/virtualMachines/sku.name   -> VM size\n# Microsoft.Storage/storageAccounts/sku.name   -> storage account tier\n# Microsoft.Network/virtualNetworks/subnets[*].name  -> subnet name (array)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Complete Custom Policy: Tag Inheritance from Resource Group"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A common custom policy requirement is ensuring that resources inherit a specific tag from their resource group. The Modify effect can copy a tag from the resource group scope down to the resource. This requires three aliases: the resource group tag value (using resourcegroup() function), the resource's own tag, and the Modify operation type set to addOrReplace."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "json"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"displayName\": \"Inherit CostCenter tag from resource group\",\n    \"mode\": \"Indexed\",\n    \"parameters\": {\n      \"tagName\": {\n        \"type\": \"String\",\n        \"metadata\": { \"displayName\": \"Tag name\", \"description\": \"Tag to inherit\" },\n        \"defaultValue\": \"CostCenter\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"policyRule\": {\n      \"if\": {\n        \"allOf\": [\n          {\n            \"field\": \"[concat('tags[', parameters('tagName'), ']')]\",\n            \"notEquals\": \"[resourceGroup().tags[parameters('tagName')]]\"\n          },\n          {\n            \"value\": \"[resourceGroup().tags[parameters('tagName')]]\",\n            \"notEquals\": \"\"\n          }\n        ]\n      },\n      \"then\": {\n        \"effect\": \"modify\",\n        \"details\": {\n          \"roleDefinitionIds\": [\n            \"/providers/Microsoft.Authorization/roleDefinitions/b24988ac-6180-42a0-ab88-20f7382dd24c\"\n          ],\n          \"operations\": [\n            {\n              \"operation\": \"addOrReplace\",\n              \"field\": \"[concat('tags[', parameters('tagName'), ']')]\",\n              \"value\": \"[resourceGroup().tags[parameters('tagName')]]\"\n            }\n          ]\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}"
