          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An Azure Policy rule consists of an if condition block and a then effect block. The if block uses field conditions (equals, in, like, exists) combined with logical operators (allOf, anyOf, not) and count expressions for array properties. The then block specifies the effect (Deny, Audit, AuditIfNotExists, DeployIfNotExists, Append, Modify, DenyAction, or Disabled) and, for AINE and DINE, a details section describing the companion resource and existence check. Parameters inject configurable values using [parameters('name')] ARM function syntax. Policy aliases are the property paths for field references \u2014 use az policy alias list to discover correct alias strings before authoring a new policy."
